#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:5
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "介紹"

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:7
msgid ""
"This document covers the Linux Kernel to Userspace API's used by video and "
"radio streaming devices, including video cameras, analog and digital TV "
"receiver cards, AM/FM receiver cards, Software Defined Radio (SDR), "
"streaming capture and output devices, codec devices and remote controllers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:12
msgid ""
"A typical media device hardware is shown at :ref:`typical_media_device`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:16
msgid "typical_media_device.svg"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:20
msgid "Typical Media Device"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:22
msgid ""
"The media infrastructure API was designed to control such devices. It is "
"divided into five parts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:25
msgid ""
"The :ref:`first part <v4l2spec>` covers radio, video capture and output, "
"cameras, analog TV devices and codecs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:28
msgid ""
"The :ref:`second part <dvbapi>` covers the API used for digital TV and "
"Internet reception via one of the several digital tv standards. While it is "
"called as DVB API, in fact it covers several different video standards "
"including DVB-T/T2, DVB-S/S2, DVB-C, ATSC, ISDB-T, ISDB-S, DTMB, etc. The "
"complete list of supported standards can be found at :c:type:"
"`fe_delivery_system`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:35
msgid ""
"The :ref:`third part <remote_controllers>` covers the Remote Controller API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:37
msgid ""
"The :ref:`fourth part <media_controller>` covers the Media Controller API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:39
msgid ""
"The :ref:`fifth part <cec>` covers the CEC (Consumer Electronics Control) "
"API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/intro.rst:41
msgid ""
"It should also be noted that a media device may also have audio components, "
"like mixers, PCM capture, PCM playback, etc, which are controlled via ALSA "
"API.  For additional information and for the latest development code, see: "
"`https://linuxtv.org <https://linuxtv.org>`__.  For discussing improvements, "
"reporting troubles, sending new drivers, etc, please mail to: `Linux Media "
"Mailing List (LMML) <http://vger.kernel.org/vger-lists.html#linux-media>`__."
msgstr ""
